<h1>Tutorial 39. Finishing the Hem of the Skirt.</h1>
<p></p>
<p><strong>I take a bias tape and sew it on along both edges.</strong> The color of the upper thread matches that of the bias tape. The bobbin thread stays the same as before. The edges of the bias tape are heat-sealed.</p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image002.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image004.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image006.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image008.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>The bias tape is secured in place.</strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image010.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></strong></p>
<p><strong>Before reinforcing the hem with a bone, I sew on a small piece of bias tape to overlay the joint between its ends. </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image012.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I put down a wide Rigilene bone and sew it on along both edges.</strong> I have swapped the upper thread with the bobbin thread: now the dark thread is in the bobbin and the light thread is at the top to match the color of the bone.</p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image014.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image016.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image018.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I overlay the joint between the two ends of the bone and stitch it up.</strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image020.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>The bone is now sewn on. All seams on the bias tape match its color. </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image022.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I still need to sew on the last row of ruffles. </strong>I swap back to the thread I used for sewing on the ruffles.&nbsp; You are supposed to repeat the configuration of the bottom row of ruffles while making sure not to sew the new ruffle on higher than 3-4cm from the edge of the skirt.&nbsp; </p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image024.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>I start sewing. </strong>I sew right along the bone in the straight areas and keep easing in as I sew. Whenever the ruffle ends, I put down a ruffle of the other color. If there is a detached ruffle tail left at the end of the sewing, I arrange it in the second row and sew it on. </p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image026.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image028.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image030.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image032.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/Premium-Dress/transcripts/Tutorial%2039_files/image034.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>The entire hem of the skirt is finished this way.&nbsp; </strong></p>

</div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody -->
